          "Created By:"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "All your life you had empathy for animals. You wanted to be everything that dealt with their welfare - which is what made you such a big target. maybe that is why they chose you; they were looking for the edge that you had naturally, compassion. PETA recruited you and sent you to a fur farm with only a handheld camera and mace if any humans asked you for a warrant. Your hand trembled at the bloody, still live corpses of the wordless victims around you. You burn the placd down in anger, giving the animals a heroes funeral, and humans a cowards death. Your sire stood at your side, a skinless hand on your shoulder as you both watched your handy work. It turned out that the same fur farm you burnt to the ground had been a death camp of sorts for Cainites of the Black Hand, where their enemies forced them into animal forms, either by the prisoners own discipline or Vissicitude, and tortured by having their skin constantly torn from their bodies during the day by the humans, and then the Inquisition came in the night to interrogate. As it appears, you and your sire are the only witnesses to these atrocities, and sometimes the stares from your Pack Mates and new Cainite family make you wonder if they had ever existed at all. Your sire embraced you to use you as a tool to locate and destroy more of these farms, as the Pack Priest you use your spiritualistic sway within the pack and knowledge of corrupt companies to lead your pack toward these farms that your sire informs you of. Up until the last 10 years your sire would go with you on these missions, slipping away in the night while your pack reveled in their latest catch, to bring Final Death to the weak and liberate the strong to rejoin the fight."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Bernie Whelay",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Nosferatu - Repulsive"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1990.0",
